problem:
Central angles $a$,$b$, and $c$ separate the circle into regions which are $\frac{1}{3}$, $\frac{1}{4}$, and $\frac{1}{6}$ of the area of the circle respectively. How many degrees are there in central angle $d$?

[asy]
draw(circle((0,0),1));
draw((0,0)--(1,0));
draw((0,0)--(0,1));
draw((0,0)--(1/2,-sqrt(3)/2));
draw((0,0)--(-sqrt(3)/2,-1/2));
label("$b$",(0,0),NE);
label("$c$",(0,0),dir(-30));
label("$d$",(0,0),dir(-100));
label("$a$",(0,0),NW);
[/asy]
